442 void CPosTracker::WriteChanges(float newVal, EReplayToken setToken, EReplayToken velToken, float tolerance)
443 {
444  float predicted=m_calculated_last+m_vel;
445  float d=newVal-predicted;
446  if (fabs(d) > tolerance)
447  {
448  m_calculated_last=newVal;
449  sWriteFloat(setToken,newVal);
450 
451  m_vel=newVal-m_actual_last;
452  sWriteFloat(velToken,m_vel);
453  }
454  else
455  {
456  m_calculated_last=predicted;
457  }
458  m_actual_last=newVal;
459 }

461 CTrackingInfo::CTrackingInfo()
462 {
463  m_id=0xffffffff;
464  mPointerType=UNDEFINED;
465  mpMovingObject=NULL;
466  mFlags=0;
467  mScale=1.0f;
468 
469  mReplayVel.Set();
470  mReplayLastPos.Set();
471  mActualLastPos.Set();
472 
473  // Making sure this won't match the object's matrix on the first frame so that
474  // changes will get recorded for the first frame.
475  mLastMatrix[0][0]=0.0f;
476 
477  m_primaryController.Reset();
478 
479  mpNext=spTrackingInfoHead;
480  mpPrevious=NULL;
481  if (mpNext)
482  {
483  mpNext->mpPrevious=this;
484  }
485  spTrackingInfoHead=this;
486 }
487 
488 CTrackingInfo::~CTrackingInfo()
489 {
490  if (mpPrevious) mpPrevious->mpNext=mpNext;
491  if (mpNext) mpNext->mpPrevious=mpPrevious;
492  if (!mpPrevious) spTrackingInfoHead=mpNext;
493 
494  sTrackingInfoHashTable.FlushItem((uint32)m_id);
495 }

518 void CTrackingInfo::RecordPositionAndAngleChanges(Mth::Vector &actual_pos, Mth::Vector &actual_angles, bool exact)
519 {
520  if (exact)
521  {
522  sWriteSingleToken(SET_POSITION_ANGLES);
523  sWriteFloat(actual_pos[X]);
524  sWriteFloat(actual_pos[Y]);
525  sWriteFloat(actual_pos[Z]);
526  sWriteFloat(actual_angles[X]);
527  sWriteFloat(actual_angles[Y]);
528  sWriteFloat(actual_angles[Z]);
529  return;
530  }
531 
532  // Compare the actual position with that predicted by the last
533  // position and velocity
534  Mth::Vector predicted_pos=mReplayLastPos+mReplayVel;
535  Mth::Vector d=actual_pos-predicted_pos;
536 
537  if (fabs(d[X]) > 0.1f || fabs(d[Y]) > 0.1f || fabs(d[Z]) > 0.1f)
538  {
539  mReplayLastPos=actual_pos;
540  sWriteVector(SET_POSITION,actual_pos);
541 
542 
543  mReplayVel=actual_pos-mActualLastPos;
544  sWriteVector(SET_VELOCITY,mReplayVel);
545  }
546  else
547  {
548  mReplayLastPos=predicted_pos;
549  }
550  mActualLastPos=actual_pos;
551 
552 
553  // Do the angles.
554  mTrackerAngleX.WriteChanges(actual_angles[X],SET_ANGLE_X,SET_ANGULAR_VELOCITY_X);
555  mTrackerAngleY.WriteChanges(actual_angles[Y],SET_ANGLE_Y,SET_ANGULAR_VELOCITY_Y);
556  mTrackerAngleZ.WriteChanges(actual_angles[Z],SET_ANGLE_Z,SET_ANGULAR_VELOCITY_Z);
557 }

952 void CDummy::UpdateLoopingSound()
953 {
954  if (!m_looping_sound_checksum)
955  {
956  return;
957  }
958 
959  float percent_of_max_speed=100.0f;
960  float maxSpeed = 1100.0f;
961  Mth::Vector v=m_pos-m_old_pos;
962  v[Y]=0.0f;
963  float speed = v.Length( ) * 60.0f;
964  if ( fabsf( speed ) < maxSpeed )
965  {
966  percent_of_max_speed=( 100.0f * speed ) / maxSpeed;
967  }
968 
969  Sfx::CSfxManager * sfx_manager = Sfx::CSfxManager::Instance();
970 
971  if (!m_looping_sound_id)
972  {
973  m_looping_sound_id = sfx_manager->PlaySound( m_looping_sound_checksum, 0, 0 );
974  }
975 
976  Sfx::sVolume vol;
977  sfx_manager->SetVolumeFromPos( &vol, m_pos, sfx_manager->GetDropoffDist( m_looping_sound_checksum ) );
978 
979  vol.PercentageAdjustment( percent_of_max_speed );
980 
981  float pitch = PERCENT( m_pitch_max - m_pitch_min, percent_of_max_speed );
982  pitch += m_pitch_min;
983 
984  sfx_manager->UpdateLoopingSound(m_looping_sound_id,&vol,pitch);
985 }

1537 static uint32 sReadAnimControllerChanges(uint32 offset, Gfx::CAnimChannel *p_anim_controller)
1538 {
1539  #define MAX_CHANGES 18
1540  uint8 p_buf[5*MAX_CHANGES];
1541 
1542  uint8 num_changes;
1543  ReadFromBuffer(&num_changes,offset,1);
1544  ++offset;
1545  Dbg_MsgAssert(num_changes<=MAX_CHANGES,("Too many anim controller changes in one instruction"));
1546 
1547  ReadFromBuffer(p_buf,offset,5*num_changes);
1548  offset+=5*num_changes;
1549 
1550  uint32 *p_dest=(uint32*)p_anim_controller;
1551  uint8 *p_foo=p_buf;
1552  for (int i=0; i<num_changes; ++i)
1553  {
1554  uint8 off=*p_foo++;
1555  Dbg_MsgAssert(off<sizeof(Gfx::CAnimChannel)/4,("Bad offset of %d in anim controller change instruction",off));
1556  p_dest[off]=Script::Read4Bytes(p_foo).mUInt;

1561 }

1564 #define TRICK_TEXT_BUF_SIZE 5000
1565 static char spTrickText[TRICK_TEXT_BUF_SIZE];
1566 // TODO: This is duplicated in score.cpp, move it to a header ...
1567 const int TRICK_LIMIT = 250;
1568 
1569 #ifdef CHECK_TOKEN_USAGE
1570 static int sTokenCount[NUM_REPLAY_TOKEN_TYPES];
1571 #endif
1572 
1573 // If the offset points to a frame, ie data that starts with the FRAME_START token, it will
1574 // skip over it and return the new offset.
1575 // If nothing follows the frame, it will set the contents of p_nothingFollows to true, false otherwise.
1576 // Nothing follows the frame if either it is followed by a BLANK token, or if the offset following
1577 // it is the end of the big buffer.
1578 //
1579 // If offset does not point to a FRAME_START token, then the returned offset will be unchanged.
1580 static uint32 sReadFrame(uint32 offset, bool *p_nothingFollows, EDummyList whichList)
1581 {
1582  Dbg_MsgAssert(p_nothingFollows,("NULL p_nothingFollows"));
1583  Dbg_MsgAssert(offset<GetBufferSize(),("Bad offset sent to sReadFrame"));
1584 
1585  #ifdef CHECK_TOKEN_USAGE
1586  for (int i=0; i<NUM_REPLAY_TOKEN_TYPES; ++i)
1587  {
1588  sTokenCount[i]=0;
1589  }
1590  #endif
1591 
1592 
1593  uint8 token;
1594  ReadFromBuffer(&token,offset,1);
1595  if (token!=FRAME_START)
1596  {
1597  *p_nothingFollows=true;
1598  return offset;
1599  }
1600  offset+=5;
1601 
1602 
1603  Obj::CSkater *p_skater=sGetSkater();
1604 
1605  Lst::HashTable<CDummy> *p_dummy_table=sGetDummyHashTable(whichList);
1606  *p_nothingFollows=false;
1607  CDummy *p_dummy=NULL;
1608  bool end=false;
1609  while (!end)
1610  {
1611  if (offset==GetBufferSize())
1612  {
1613  *p_nothingFollows=true;
1614  break;
1615  }
1616  Dbg_MsgAssert(offset<GetBufferSize(),("sReadFrame went past the end of the buffer"));
1617 
1618  ReadFromBuffer(&token,offset,1);
1619 
1620  #ifdef CHECK_TOKEN_USAGE
1621  Dbg_MsgAssert(token<NUM_REPLAY_TOKEN_TYPES,("Bad token"));
1622  ++sTokenCount[token];
1623  #endif
1624 
1625  switch (token)
1626  {
1627  case BLANK:
1628  *p_nothingFollows=true;
1629  end=true;
1630  break;
1631 
1632  case FRAME_START:
1633  end=true;
1634  break;
1635 
1636  case SCREEN_BLUR:
1637  {
1638  // Must not do blurs if recording
1639  if (sMode==RECORD)
1640  {
1641  offset+=1+4;
1642  break;
1643  }
1644 
1645  ++offset;
1646  int amount;
1647  ReadFromBuffer((uint8*)&amount,offset,4);
1648  amount=Script::Read4Bytes((uint8*)&amount).mInt;
1649  offset+=4;
1650 
1651  Nx::CEngine::sSetScreenBlur(amount);
1652  break;
1653  }
1654 
1655  case SCREEN_FLASH:
1656  {
1657  // Must not do flashes if recording
1658  if (sMode==RECORD)
1659  {
1660  offset+=1+4*6;
1661  break;
1662  }
1663 
1664  ++offset;
1665 
1666  int viewport;
1667  ReadFromBuffer((uint8*)&viewport,offset,4);
1668  viewport=Script::Read4Bytes((uint8*)&viewport).mInt;
1669  offset+=4;
1670 
1671  Image::RGBA from;
1672  ReadFromBuffer((uint8*)&from,offset,4);
1673  offset+=4;
1674 
1675  Image::RGBA to;
1676  ReadFromBuffer((uint8*)&to,offset,4);
1677  offset+=4;
1678 
1679  float duration;
1680  ReadFromBuffer((uint8*)&duration,offset,4);
1681  duration=Script::Read4Bytes((uint8*)&duration).mFloat;
1682  offset+=4;
1683 
1684  float z;
1685  ReadFromBuffer((uint8*)&z,offset,4);
1686  z=Script::Read4Bytes((uint8*)&z).mFloat;
1687  offset+=4;
1688 
1689  uint32 flags;
1690  ReadFromBuffer((uint8*)&flags,offset,4);
1691  flags=Script::Read4Bytes((uint8*)&flags).mUInt;
1692  offset+=4;
1693 
1694  flags|=Nx::SCREEN_FLASH_FLAG_IGNORE_PAUSE;
1695 
1696  Nx::AddScreenFlash(viewport,from,to,duration,z,flags,NULL);
1697  break;
1698  }
1699 
1700  case SHATTER_PARAMS:
1701  {

1704  {
1705  offset+=1+4*9;

2991 // After calling this, sBigBufferEndOffset will be guaranteed to point to enough contiguous space
2992 // to hold frameSize bytes.
2993 static void sMakeEnoughSpace(uint32 frameSize)
2994 {
2995  // This loop makes one modification to the buffer each time around, and breaks out once
2996  // enough space has been freed.
2997  while (true)
2998  {
2999  if (sBigBufferStartOffset < sBigBufferEndOffset)
3000  {
3001  Dbg_MsgAssert(sBigBufferStartOffset==0,("sBigBufferStartOffset not zero ?"));
3002 
3003  // We know that all the space from sBigBufferEndOffset to the end of the buffer
3004  // is free to use, so check if that space is big enough.
3005  if (GetBufferSize()-sBigBufferEndOffset >= frameSize)
3006  {
3007  // It is!
3008  break;
3009  }
3010  else
3011  {
3012  // Wrap the end offset around to the start of the buffer, so that next time
3013  // around this loop frames at the start will start getting chomped up to make space.
3014  sBigBufferEndOffset=0;
3015 
3016  sBufferFilling=false;
3017  }
3018  }
3019  else if (sBigBufferStartOffset > sBigBufferEndOffset)
3020  {
3021  // The space between end and start is free to use, so check if it is big enough.
3022  if (sBigBufferStartOffset-sBigBufferEndOffset >= frameSize)
3023  {
3024  // It is!
3025  break;
3026  }
3027  else
3028  {
3029  // Skip the start offset over the frame it is pointing to.
3030  bool nothing_follows=false;
3031  uint32 old_start=sBigBufferStartOffset;
3032  sBigBufferStartOffset=sReadFrame(sBigBufferStartOffset,&nothing_follows,START_STATE_DUMMY_LIST);
3033  if (sBigBufferStartOffset==old_start)
3034  {
3035  // The start offset did not move, meaning it is pointing to empty space.
3036  // The only time this should happen is when the buffer is empty, in which
3037  // case the start and end offset should both be zero. So assert.
3038  Dbg_MsgAssert(0,("Start offset points to empty space, even though it is greater than end offset ?"));
3039 
3040  // Just in case this does ever happen on a release build, reset the buffer so that
3041  // it does not hang. All that will happen is that the replay will be lost.
3042  sDeleteDummies(START_STATE_DUMMY_LIST);
3043  sDeleteDummies(PLAYBACK_DUMMY_LIST);
3044  Dbg_MsgAssert(spReplayDummies==NULL,("Hey! spReplayDummies not NULL !!!"));
3045  sDeleteObjectTrackingInfo();
3046  ClearBuffer();
3047  }
3048  else
3049  {
3050  // Fill the frame just skipped over with BLANK's
3051  FillBuffer(old_start,sBigBufferStartOffset-old_start,BLANK);
3052  // Wrap around if necessary.
3053  if (nothing_follows)
3054  {
3055  sBigBufferStartOffset=0;
3056  }
3057  }
3058  }
3059  }
3060  else
3061  {
3062  // sBigBufferStartOffset equals sBigBufferEndOffset
3063  bool nothing_follows=false;
3064  uint32 old_start=sBigBufferStartOffset;
3065  sBigBufferStartOffset=sReadFrame(sBigBufferStartOffset,&nothing_follows,START_STATE_DUMMY_LIST);
3066  if (sBigBufferStartOffset==old_start)
3067  {
3068  // If the start offset did not move, it must be pointing to empty space.
3069  // The only time the start offset should point to empty space is when the
3070  // buffer is totally empty, in which case the start offset would be expected to be zero.
3071  // So check that.
3072  Dbg_MsgAssert(sBigBufferStartOffset==0,("Expected sBigBufferStartOffset to be zero"));
3073  // Check that the frame size is not bigger than the entire buffer.
3074  Dbg_MsgAssert(GetBufferSize() >= frameSize,("Frame size %d too big for replay buffer",frameSize));
3075  // There is enough space, so break out.
3076  break;
3077  }
3078  else
3079  {
3080  // Fill the frame just skipped over with BLANK's
3081  FillBuffer(old_start,sBigBufferStartOffset-old_start,BLANK);
3082  // Wrap around if necessary.
3083  if (nothing_follows)
3084  {
3085  sBigBufferStartOffset=0;
3086  }
3087  }
3088  }
3089  }
3090 }

3092 static void sWriteFrameBufferToBigBuffer()
3093 {
3094  uint32 frame_size=spFrameBufferPos-spFrameBuffer;
3095 
3096  sMakeEnoughSpace(frame_size);
3097 
3098  // sBigBufferEndOffset is now guaranteed to point to enough contiguous space to
3099  // hold frame_size bytes, so write in the frame data.
3100  WriteIntoBuffer(spFrameBuffer,sBigBufferEndOffset,frame_size);
3101  sBigBufferEndOffset+=frame_size;
3102  // Wrap around if necessary.
3103  if (sBigBufferEndOffset==GetBufferSize())
3104  {
3105  sBigBufferEndOffset=0;
3106  }
3107 }

4067 //static int playback_frame=0;
4068 static void sPlayback(bool display)
4069 {
4070  // If reached the end of the replay, do nothing.
4071  if (sReachedEndOfReplay)
4072  {
4073  return;
4074  }
4075  if (sReplayPaused)
4076  {
4077  return;
4078  }
4079 
4080  Obj::CSkater *p_skater=sGetSkater();
4081  // NGC must not replay vibrations, TRC requirement.
4082  if (Config::GetHardware() != Config::HARDWARE_NGC)
4083  {
4084  if (sNeedToInitialiseVibration)
4085  {
4086  if (!sCurrentState.mSkaterPaused)
4087  {
4088  for (int i=0; i<Obj::CVibrationComponent::vVB_NUM_ACTUATORS; ++i)
4089  {
4090  p_skater->GetDevice()->ActivateActuator(i,sCurrentState.mActuatorStrength[i]);
4091  }
4092  }
4093  sNeedToInitialiseVibration=false;
4094  }
4095  }
4096 
4097  // Read the next frame
4098  bool nothing_follows=false;
4099  sNextPlaybackFrameOffset=sReadFrame(sNextPlaybackFrameOffset,&nothing_follows,PLAYBACK_DUMMY_LIST);
4100 
4101  // The process of reading the frame will have updated all the dummy's.
4102  // Now display them & do other misc stuff like update sounds.
4103  CDummy *p_dummy=spReplayDummies;
4104  while (p_dummy)
4105  {
4106  p_dummy->UpdateMutedSounds();
4107  if (display)
4108  {
4109  p_dummy->DisplayModel();
4110  }
4111  p_dummy=p_dummy->mpNext;
4112  }
4113 
4114 
4115  // Wrap around if reached the end of the replay buffer.
4116  if (sNextPlaybackFrameOffset==GetBufferSize())
4117  {
4118  sNextPlaybackFrameOffset=0;
4119  }
4120 
4121  // It is possible that the frame could be followed by some space filled with
4122  // BLANK, so skip over it until either a new frame is hit or we get back
4123  // to the start frame.
4124  while (true)
4125  {
4126  uint8 token;
4127  ReadFromBuffer(&token,sNextPlaybackFrameOffset,1);
4128 
4129  if (token != BLANK)
4130  {
4131  // Hit a new frame
4132  Dbg_MsgAssert(token==FRAME_START,("Expected token to be FRAME_START"));
4133  break;
4134  }
4135 
4136  // sBufferFilling is a flag used to indicate that the buffer is filling up for the
4137  // first time and has not cycled around yet.
4138  // Knowing this means we don't need to read each individual byte, since we know everything
4139  // will be blank till the end of the buffer, so just set sNextPlaybackFrameOffset to 0
4140  // straight away.
4141  // This is a speed optimization for the GameCube, since it has a 4meg replay buffer, and
4142  // it takes several seconds so read all those blanks.
4143  if (sBufferFilling)
4144  {
4145  Dbg_MsgAssert(sBigBufferStartOffset==0,("Expected sBigBufferStartOffset to be zero when the buffer is filling up?"));
4146  sNextPlaybackFrameOffset=0;
4147  }
4148 
4149  if (sNextPlaybackFrameOffset==sBigBufferStartOffset)
4150  {
4151  // Reached the start again.
4152  break;
4153  }
4154 
4155  ++sNextPlaybackFrameOffset;
4156  if (sNextPlaybackFrameOffset==GetBufferSize())
4157  {
4158  sNextPlaybackFrameOffset=0;
4159  }
4160  }
4161 
4162  // If we've got back to the start, then that is the end of the replay,
4163  // so kill all the dummys and restore everything the way it was.
4164  if (sNextPlaybackFrameOffset==sBigBufferStartOffset)
4165  {
4166  // Switch off any vibrations being done by the replay, so that they do not continue
4167  // while the end-replay menu is on screen.
4168  // Note that any vibrations that were being done in-game before the replay was run will
4169  // automatically get restored when the game is un-paused, so we do not need to restore them here.
4170  sSwitchOffVibrations();
4171 
4172  sStopReplayDummyLoopingSounds();
4173 
4174  // Now that the replay has ended, the player may want to save it to mem card.
4175  // So make sure that the start-state contains the correct active/visible status of all the sectors.
4176  Nx::CEngine::sWriteSectorStatusBitfield(sStartState.mpSectorStatus,SECTOR_STATUS_BUFFER_SIZE);
4177 
4178  Script::RunScript("EndOfReplay");
4179  sReachedEndOfReplay=true;
4180  }
4181 }

4477 void Manager::s_end_frame_code( const Tsk::Task< Manager >& task )

4522  if ( CFuncs::CheckButton( pFront->GetInputHandler( i ), 0x4b358aeb ) ) // right
4523  {

4542  sPlayback();
4543  }

4545  }
